					<![CDATA[
						 <div style="text-align: right;"></div> <hr /> <div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:300px;"><img src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS9yH0JA5go418GMsLtQgpXMcgmieXmgGGuGA&amp;usqp=CAU" style="width:300px;" alt="images?q=tbn:ANd9GcS9yH0JA5go418GMsLtQgpXMcgmieXmgGGuGA&amp;usqp=CAU" class="image" /> <div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:300px;"> <p>SCP-5127; &quot;Rose-Coloured Glasses&quot;</p> </div> </div> <p><strong>Item #:</strong> SCP-5127</p> <p><strong>Object Class:</strong> Safe</p> <p><strong>Special Containment Procedures:</strong> SCP-5127 is to be kept within a standard secure storage locker at Site-64. Access requires minimum Clearance 2 while being deemed in satisfactory psychological condition by site psychiatric staff. Supervising personnel are not to look through SCP-5127 unless the object is being worn. Personnel accessing SCP-5127 are required to submit to a psychological screening after each session.</p> <p>While there is no inherent threat in not doing so, is recommended to keep SCP-5127 in a locked containment unit during transport to prevent unintended use. SCP-5127 can be transported unescorted, provided appropriate measures are taken to prevent unauthorized or accidental usage.</p> <p>While SCP-5127 otherwise maintains pristine condition, it is to receive professional polishing once annually to prevent accidental wear on the lenses.</p> <p><strong>Temporary Containment Procedure Update:</strong> (<em>See Addendum 5127.1</em>) Per Containment Committee Order 5127.S64.15.1, Dr P█████ is no longer permitted to interact directly with SCP-5127 outside of a testing environment. This order shall persist indefinitely, until such a time a consensus regarding Dr P█████'s mental state has been reached.</p> <p><strong>Description:</strong> SCP-5127 is a material object resembling circular pink spectacles<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-586988-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >1</a></sup> with no immediate exceptional qualities. The location of origin remains unknown, but the time of creation has been dated to the 1840s by Foundation anthropologists. When SCP-5127 is worn or otherwise looked through, the world seen through it instantly takes on a &quot;rosey retrospection&quot;.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-586988-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >2</a></sup> Subjects are usually aware that the cause of this effect stems from SCP-5127, and SCP-5127 can be removed from the wearer at any time. Some subjects have reported that usage of SCP-5127 is comparable to a small dosage of Ecstasy (<em>3,4-Methyl​enedioxy​methamphetamine</em>) differing only in that the effect ends immediately upon removal instead of the standard 3-6 hours. Results vary depending on the mental state and psychological triggers of the subject, but all subjects have reported a general feeling of serenity. SCP-5127's bliss-inducing properties can cause addiction in subjects subjected to long-term use.</p> <p><strong>Discovery:</strong> Purchased for £7 at ████ Antiques, an antique shop in Windsor, UK, by Foundation personnel. SCP-5127's anomalous attributes were discovered when a researcher from Site-91 &quot;tried them on&quot; before their subsequent purchase. SCP-5127 was later transferred to Site-64 after Site-91 ruled out any possible xenobiological or thaumaturgical origins.</p> <p><strong>Experiment-5127-01:</strong> Dr A███, in an attempt to test SCP-5127's effective range, propped the object into a position at which it could be viewed through, placed a portrait in front of SCP-5127, and proceeded to move backwards. Dr A███ concluded that SCP-5127's effective range was the human eye's ability to see through it. Stating that: &quot;The painting just kept getting more and more beautiful.&quot;</p> <p><strong>Experiment-5127-02:</strong> A camera was placed behind one of SCP-5127's lenses. The footage was reported to have no anomalous properties other than being pink tinted. It seems that SCP-5127 is only effective when <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">used by humans</span> (<em>See Experiment-5127-03; Experiment-5127-05</em>) directly observed by creatures that can see.</p> <p><strong>Experiment-5127-03:</strong> SCP-5127 was placed on various kinds of animals<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-586988-3" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >3</a></sup> and the status of each specimen was documented. All instances in which the subject could see through SCP-5127 reported an activation of their various pleasure centres, with increased serotonin and dopamine production.</p> <p><strong>Experiment-5127-04:</strong> One (1) D-class diagnosed with chemically-imbalanced depression was instructed to wear SCP-5127 as one usually would. The D-class reported feeling &quot;unbothered and carefree&quot; and proceeded to sing a rendition of Louis Armstrong's <em>What A Wonderful World</em>, despite there being no green trees or flowers of any kind in the vicinity. When the object had been removed from the D-class (only minimal resistance was present) the subject reported that he no longer suffered from depressive episodes, but was able to experience feelings related to sadness again.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-586988-4" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" >4</a></sup></p> <p><strong>Experiment-5127-05:</strong> One (1) D-class was given a standard tactical flashlight (250 Lumens) and asked to shine light through SCP-5127 and observe the object's effects. Upon shining the beam through SCP-5127's left lens, the beam was amplified by approximately 2.5x in brightness, with a final result of light as bright as 630 Lumens. The light produced and emitted from SCP-5127, hereby designated SCP-5127-1, has properties similar to its source of origin. The only new property exhibited by SCP-5127-1 is that its optical manipulation is observable to all sighted parties. If a sufficiently bright light source is used to create SCP-5127-1, the light produced can engulf large areas. It is impossible to burn an individual or item using the object's natural magnification properties; no matter how strong the light source.</p> <p><strong>Addendum 5127.1:</strong> Dr P█████ received SCP-5127 during its transit period from Site-91 to Site-64, where it had been previously monitored by Dr A███. For the duration of transit, and a significant measure of time while in Site-64's custody, Dr P█████ used SCP-5127 for his personal enjoyment and developed an addiction to SCP-5127's euphoric effects. Due to the lack of briefing on the effects of SCP-5127 other than: &quot;(the object) is safe to wear&quot;, administrative action has not been taken against Dr P█████. The only exception being the restriction of access to SCP-5127, which was submitted at Dr P█████'s request.</p> <p>The following interview was conducted by Site-64's psychology team after Dr P█████ was taken into custody, and SCP-5127 was placed back in containment.</p> <blockquote> <p><strong>Interviewer:</strong> Dr Andy Westenfelt, Site-64<br /> <strong>Interviewee:</strong> Dr P█████, Site-64</p> <hr /> <p>[BEGIN LOG]</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr Westenfelt:</strong> How are you feeling today Doctor-</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr P█████:</strong> (<em>In Mandarin Chinese</em>) Cut the shit, Andy.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr Westenfelt:</strong> I know I'm the only other one in the room that can speak Mandarin, but they're going to translate it anyway so you might as well use English.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr P█████:</strong> (<em>In English</em>) How the fuck do you think I feel? I'm in withdrawal.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr Westenfelt:</strong> Well, that's fair enough. Since you want to get right to it, why'd you do it?</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr P█████:</strong> (<em>Groans</em>) Could I get some water, please?</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p>(<em>Dr Westenfelt gestures, and a glass of water is brought to Dr P█████</em>)</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr Westenfelt:</strong> But why <em>did</em> you do it █████?</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr P█████:</strong> Quite frankly I didn't expect the rollercoaster I got.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr Westenfelt:</strong> Rollercoaster?</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr P█████:</strong> Well yeah, A███ said that they were safe to wear. Guess he didn't have to wear them much when they were looking for (<em>A Brief Pause</em>) magic?</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr Westenfelt:</strong> Thaumatic signatures, yeah.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr P█████:</strong> (<em>Chuckles</em>) Well that's Yorkshire for you.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p>(<em>Both doctors continue the friendly conversation for a while until Dr Westenfelt redirects back to the main topic</em>)</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr Westenfelt:</strong> So how was the experience?</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr P█████:</strong> Nice at first. Everybody wants to stress a little less, but it just got worse.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr Westenfelt:</strong> Could you define &quot;worse&quot; for me?</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr P█████:</strong> Well, okay. So imagine being a tad bit drunk, but all the time. You are happy, warm, not a care in the world. Yet you <em>know</em> that people are looking at you a little funny, but that doesn't make you want to stop, right? You consider it, so you take 'em off but the world is just so painstakingly dull. Before you know it they're right back on your face and you won't think about this again for a week. It was like that if that makes any sense.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr Westenfelt:</strong> Would you consider using (SCP-5127) again?</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr P█████:</strong> Well maybe. (<em>A Brief Pause</em>) Actually no. Not unless I needed to. In fact, keep it away from me, okay? I know that withdrawal gets worse before it gets better and I don't want easy access to it in case I start slipping.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p><strong>Dr Westenfelt:</strong> I'll see what I can do.<br /> [END LOG]</p> </blockquote> <p>Dr P█████ has since been rehabilitated and has resumed his research at Site-64 with his previous clearance. At his request, Containment Committee Order 5127.S64.15.1 remains in place.</p> <p><strong>Addendum 5127.2:</strong> While being tested at Site-91, Dr A███ remarked on how SCP-5127's euphoria-inducing qualities could be implicated to assist any individuals infected with <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4042" target="_blank">SCP-4042</a>. This request is pending, but the Foundation's consistent attempts to monitor and contain instances of <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4042" target="_blank">SCP-4042-2</a> continue.</p> <p><em>Scribe's note:</em> This document was originally composed at Site-91 before being amended and completed by Site-64. SCP-5127 was originally contained and documented in the United Kingdom before being transferred to a facility in the United States. Therefore, it is composed in British-English to preserve its comprehensive integrity.</p> <p>by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/izaacpowers" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=6533554&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610202597" alt="IzaacPowers" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=6533554)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/izaacpowers" >IzaacPowers</a></span></p> <div class="footnotes-footer"> <div class="title">Footnotes</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-586988-1"><a href="javascript:;" >1</a>. Also known as &quot;glasses&quot;</div> <div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-586988-2